{
  "stem": "11611.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The Germans surrendered in May '45, and we were planning, as a training exercise, to take Wake Island, which the Japanese had taken at the beginning of the war.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we figured that was a low casualty operation.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I should say, Iwo Jima was within 500 miles of Tokyo.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So we didn't have anywhere to go except Japan from Iwo Jima.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we-- my division was designated to be the first backup division on the landings in Tokyo Bay, which would be absolutely the worst position in a landing that you can conceive because the-- with the assault, two divisions assault, would probably take heavy, heavy casualties.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But we were likely to take casualties in landing, and then we'd be the infantry that would do the fighting in Tokyo Bay.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So our expectations were not very good.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, several things happened, some of them scheduled and some of them unknown to us.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We knew by that time that the Russians were going to come into the war by sometime the first week in August.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We didn't know that we were going to drop atomic bombs in the first week in August, which we did.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Not by accident, the bombs were dropped a couple of days before the Russian entry in Manchuria.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And of course, by that time I had a good friend of mine.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He was a-- he was working on a doctorate in history in California.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We did an article probably in the spring of '45 for publication in which we tried to anticipate how the hell the war would ever end.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "By June, the Japanese were looking for peace.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They were negotiating in Switzerland.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
